<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1436,386,915]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,316,531,555]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[323,476,531,555]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Xerometra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trichombra">
<emphasis box="[323,476,531,555]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">P. trichombra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<specimenCount box="[706,842,530,554]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
from Broken Hill collected in October by Lower. We have examined the female 
<typeStatus box="[457,547,567,591]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">syntype</typeStatus>
, dated 
<date box="[630,708,566,590]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" value="1897-10">x.1897</date>
, in coll. Meyrick (slide no. 30950). Its abdomen is damaged by fungal hyphae but the partially preserved genitalia with a long, narrow, distally pointed sclerotization in the antrum indicate a close relationship with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li &amp; Sattler" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[527,665,638,662]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Mesophleps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mylicotis">
<emphasis box="[527,550,639,662]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[564,665,638,662]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">mylicotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A 
<typeStatus box="[707,809,638,662]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">lectotype</typeStatus>
should be designated from the Lower collection (SAM, Adelaide). The female genitalia agree with those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li &amp; Sattler" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[742,843,675,699]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Mesophleps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mylicotis">
<emphasis box="[742,843,675,699]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">mylicotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the long, pointed sclerotization of the antrum but differ in the much longer apophyses. In the apophyses anteriores the base is not so clearly divided into a ventral and a dorsal branch as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li &amp; Sattler" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[388,489,747,771]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Mesophleps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mylicotis">
<emphasis box="[388,489,747,771]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">mylicotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
